Gym Platform
Project Goal

The main goal of this project is the development of a full-stack web application that enables users to manage their physical progress in a structured and scientifically based way.

The application should provide:

Systematic workout tracking – digitalization of the training process through recording sets, repetitions, and working weights, allowing users to track progressive overload over time.

Nutrition management – precise control of daily calorie intake and macronutrients (proteins, fats, and carbohydrates) according to personalized user goals.

Technologies
1. Frontend

The user interface is a React web application that communicates with the server via REST API requests.

2. Backend

A Python Flask application is used to serve the client and communicate directly with the database.
It is responsible for processing all REST API requests sent by the client.

3. Database

A MySQL database is used for persistent storage of all information related to users, workouts, and nutrition.

It is connected to Flask through the SQLAlchemy ORM, which simplifies working with data through Python code.

4. Caching

To improve application performance, Redis will be used as an in-memory data store.

Core Functionalities
1. Authentication

User registration – creating a new account by entering basic information (first name, last name, email, password, date of birth).

Login system – user authentication using email and password.

JWT Security – after successful login, the server issues a JSON Web Token (JWT) that is stored on the frontend (React) and sent with each API request to verify user identity.

Password hashing – passwords are never stored as plain text. Libraries such as bcrypt are used to securely hash passwords before storing them in the database.

The application supports two roles:

Administrator

User

Administrator Panel

Exercise catalog management – adding, editing, and deleting exercises in the global system (exercise name, description, primary muscle group).

Nutrition database – adding and validating food items and their nutritional values available to all users.

Dashboard

The dashboard provides an overview of the user's current daily status.

Nutrition status – shows remaining calories and protein until the daily goal is reached.

Last workout – short information about the last workout session and routine performed.

Quick Start button – allows users to quickly start a workout or log a meal.

Workout Module

This module is divided into three phases:

Routine Creator

Users can select exercises from the catalog (created by the administrator) and define the number of planned sets and weights.
Users can also modify their routines.

Routine Overview

Displays all saved routines (e.g. Push, Pull, Legs) and allows the user to choose which routine to perform that day.

Active Workout

Timer – automatic workout duration tracking

Result input – fields for entering actual weight and repetitions

Users mark completed sets using a checkbox

Clicking Save permanently stores the workout data in the history for that date

Nutrition Module

Calculator – input parameters for calculating BMI and target intake (calories, proteins, fats, carbohydrates) based on the user's goal.

Daily Log – adding meals throughout the day.

The application automatically sums all food entries and compares them with the defined nutritional goal.

Profile

Personal data management – editing and managing user information.

Additional Features

Progress visualization – line charts showing body weight and strength progression.

Workout calendar – calendar highlighting days when workouts were completed.

Progress tracking – automatic tracking of exercise performance.

Gym map – using the user's location, the application displays nearby gyms and fitness centers.

Gym information – users can see basic gym information (name, address, working hours).

Caching frequently used data

Email confirmation via SMTP (e.g. Gmail)

Notifications/reminders if workouts or meals have not been logged for a long time

Smart food search with autocomplete

